ANC President Cde Cyril Ramaphosa delivers the closing address on conclusion of the ANC NEC Lekgotla. JOHANNESBURG - The ANC NEC Lekgotla has undertaken to prioritise matters of immigration to ensure that anti-African sentiments don't take a bad turn. Concerns about the outbreak of xenophobic violence have been flagged as the "Put South Africans First" movements gain traction. READ: Unemployed SA youth demand restaurant jobs This week, the EFF conducted restaurant inspections to check the employment ratio between South African citizens and foreign nationals. The Patriotic Alliance also conducted inspections of foreign-owned shops in Eldorado Park. The ANC will need to lead the debate on immigration in order to ensure that it remains infused with principles of pan-Africanism and is not overtaken by right-wing sentiments.https://t.co/Mnxq6isXoz ANC president Cyril Ramaphosa said, "the ANC will need to lead the debate on immigration to ensure that it remains infused with principles of pan-Africanism and is not overtaken by right-wing sentiments." "Promoting legal migration is a central aspect of securing the peace and security of SA and the subregion and the ANC must act against the stoking of anti-African sentiment." ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa delivered the outcomes of the NEC Lekgotla this weekend.